'''Lothron''' was an [[Elvish]] name for the fifth month of the year. Lothron comes from the [[Sindarin]] language, and in the [[Third Age]] the name was used only by the [[Dúnedain]]. Most other calendars in [[Middle-earth]] at that time used the [[Quenya]] equivalent, which was [[Lótessë]].<ref>{{App|Calendars}}</ref> Both these names come ultimately from the [[Elvish]] root-word lot(h), 'flower', and refer to the springtime blossoming associated with this month.

